The <strong><code>id</code> <a href="/en-US/docs/Glossary/global_attribute">global attribute</a></strong> defines an identifier (ID) which must be unique in the whole document. Its purpose is to identify the element when linking (using a <a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Basics_of_HTTP/Identifying_resources_on_the_Web#Fragment">fragment identifier</a>), scripting, or styling (with <a href="/en-US/docs/Glossary/CSS">CSS</a>).